metadata.name: Alleles #339
metadata.description:
An allele, short for 'allelomorph', is an alternative version of a specific gene.

This collection (which is in no way scientifically accurate), was born out of an exercise in simplicity. Outputs are made up of arrangements of squares in various compositions, yet within that we are free to imagine what they could mean. For some, the resulting shapes might represent DNA strands or atoms. Others might see cells or the building blocks of the hereditary instructions that shape us as individuals. 

A generative genetic report accompanies each output to spark the imagination and attempt to attach further meaning to each composition. Some gene sequences carry mutations, however not all mutations are visually apparent. Please refer to the fxhash features to view the reports accordingly.

Texture is used subtly, so for maximum enjoyment it is recommended that you save and view your outputs at full size in order to best enjoy the details.

Press 'S' to save a 2400 x 3396 px PNG file.

attributes.value: Exploration of available data indicates that suggests subject may develop a psychological profile prone to infrequent episodes of grandiosity and laughter during inappropriate moments, yet also shows a rare level of [REDACTED] and foresight. metadata.name: Natt #11
metadata.description:
Natt is a short exploration of a view. On not so recent travels I captured a photo of a small town across a large body of water. It was night and the photograph was blurry, but the emotion stayed with me. It was an emotion of calm and tranquility, accepting the darkness of night and knowing that across the water was a group of people living together, creating a beacon of light. 

Natt is the generative take on this photograph, attempting to capture the same emotion in a purely digital format. 


Press “space” to pause the animation and “s” to save the current view.

For higher resolutions, add “?pd=x” (x being a number >1) to the url when in live view and refresh, then press “s” to save. Note, for higher values of “x” rendering will take longer, start with a low number like 2-3 and work your way up to the desired size. 


Generative artwork by Tengil, 2022.

For licenses see bundle.js.LICENSE.txt.

metadata.name: Primordial #242
metadata.description:
Primordial is a study of abstract forms. The algorithm, written in p5.js and WebGL, utilizes domain warping to create twisted fields of color and then overlays thousands of tiny lines to provide depth and texture. The outputs are chaotic but not completely formless, like a swirling mass of plasma from the early universe, or a strange proto-life form suspended in prehistoric ooze.

CONTROLS:

1-9: Increase resolution and save image in PNG format

B: Toggle borders on/off

F: Fullscreen
P: Portrait
L: Landscape
S: Square

For third party license information, please see license.md

David Brice Allen
October 2022

metadata.name: ____ - Iteration 3 #101
metadata.description:
This project is part of a larger experiment that explores and celebrates the process of making generative art by progressively releasing iterations, working towards a final release on my main account (tz1RkYY3jr1ocuPdQqrRefr5FqoawKQsmBmD). The iterations will be titled ____ - Iteration 1, ____ - Iteration 2, etc. At this point, the number of iterations has not been determined, but more information will be provided as this experiment unfolds.

The final release will only be made available to those who have collected each iteration (using an allowlist), and will be released for free.

In live mode, add &size=<YOUR_PIXEL_SIZE> to change the pixel size of the image for export (Right click to save). For example, &size=4000 will set the width of the image to be 4000 pixels.

metadata.name: Évasion #105
metadata.description:
This project is inspired by a familiar landscape.
 
It combines several things: a realistic dune landscape, minimalist ocean and sky, and a surrealist window at the centre.

The window deliberately presents a brighter ocean, where the sun is reflected, with waves and veils caught in the wind. It aims at representing what inspires us, what calms us, what makes us feel at home. This window extracts us from our daily thoughts and stress.


So I named this project "Évasion", a French word, which could be translated as "Escape" in English.


In this project, I decided that, even though each output will be unique and will have its own features, it will be possible, in live mode, to show/hide some elements of the project. This will allow each one of you to adapt the project to what is most relevant to you and save it.

This does not change the unique features of your mint, but you can adapt it to your preferences, to what "Évasion" means to you.



Consequently, in live mode, multiple options are available.

You can display the output with different pixel densities for a better resolution:

 - press [2] to display a 2000 x 2000 pixels output (display by default)
 - press [3] to display a 3000 x 3000 pixels output
 - press [4] to display a 4000 x 4000 pixels output (may take a moment)


You can also toggle different elements of the output, even though these features are not part of your mint:

 - press [d] to toggle the visibility of the dune
 - press [v] to toggle the visibility of the veils
 - press [t] to toggle the visibility of the sun texture
 - press [w] to toggle the visibility of the window shadow
 - press [a] to toggle the visibility of the sun rays
 - press [r] to reload


To save the output as it is displayed:

 - press [s] on a computer
 - double tap on a mobile device


On the contrary, some elements cannot be changed, such as the color palette, the place of the window and sun, the appearence of the dune, the texture, the format, etc.


Main features of this project include:

- Palette: 9 color palettes,
- Margin: Thin or Large,
- Texture: None, Soft or Strong,
- Format: 1:1, 4:5 - Portrait or 4:5 - Landscape,
- Veils: True or False,
- Rays: True or False,
- Sun Texture: True or False.


Thank you so much to all the collectors <3


Created with p5.js

metadata.name: The Restoration Scheme: Bleaching #2
metadata.description:
“Bleaching” is the third episode of “The Restoration Scheme” Series. The work was based on Acropora digitifera. 

Corals derive their colors from symbiotic algae. With the change of environment, such as rising water temperature, symbiotic algae leave the coral and therefore it becomes white. Coral bleaching does not mean death, but it does mean that the coral has lost its source of nutrients without symbiotic algae. The coral will be starving to death little by little if the environment does not improve.

——

“The Restoration Scheme” Series
It’s a virtual action extended from the coral restoration plan led by Delta Electronics Foundation from Taiwan, consisting of five generative corals. Each of them was based on five different species of coral as the theme.
If collectors mint virtual corals, Delta Electronics Foundation will drop coral seedlings collectively in the sea. 

The project is powered by FAB DAO (Formosa Art Bank). The split will donate to the local organization from Taiwan dedicated to the coral restoration scheme.

——

About Delta 
Climate change is causing irreversible impacts. Coral reefs, known for their rich biodiversity and the capability to nourish a quarter of marine life, are at the forefront of the crisis. Also known as "tropical rainforests" in the sea, coral reefs have experienced five mass bleaching events in the past five years. Once global warming exceeds the 2˚C thresholds, it's likely that 99% of coral reefs will die off worldwide.

In addition to launching a coral restoration initiative along the northeast coast of Taiwan, Delta Electronics Foundation collaborates with Asia University to host "Earth Pulsing: Nurturing Life Exhibition" and releases the first art NFT featuring coral restoration. Through these actions, we hope to evoke public awareness of ecological issues. For more information, please visit https://delta50.deltaww.com/initiative/sea.html

——

35 ~ 60 corals to render. You might need some patience for the result.

double click or press 's' to save as an image
made with p5.js and chroma.js

____________________________

《白化》為《恢復方案》系列第三作，品種為指形軸孔珊瑚。

珊瑚的顏色來自共生藻，隨著環境變化（如水溫上升），共生藻離開了珊瑚，珊瑚露出了白色。所以珊瑚白化其實不等於死亡，但共生藻的離開意味著珊瑚失去了養分來源。在環境沒有改善的狀況下，珊瑚就會慢慢餓死。

——

《恢復方案》
恢復方案是虛擬演算珊瑚實驗，一系列共五件的生成珊瑚作品，每一件對應到特定珊瑚物種。本實驗與台達電子文教基金會合作，藏家每收藏一件 NFT，台達電子文教基金會就會實際在海中植下一株對應的珊瑚苗。這項專案與 FAB DAO （福爾摩沙藝術銀行）支援鑄造，部分分潤將直接捐助給台灣在地珊瑚保育組織，詳細資訊將於 FAB DAO Twitter 公佈。

——

關於台達電子文教基金會氣候變遷引發許多不可逆的環境衝擊，以豐富生物多樣性著稱、滋養四分之一海洋生物的珊瑚，便是首當其衝的受害者。
被譽為「海中熱帶雨林」的珊瑚生態系，已在最近五年遭遇三次大白化，一旦升溫跨越攝氏2℃，屆時恐有多達99％的珊瑚瀕臨滅絕。
近年在東北角投入珊瑚復育的台達電子文教基金會，今年與亞洲大學共同策畫「地球˙脈動中」生態與藝術特展，並合作發行全台首見的珊瑚生成藝術NFT，喚起社會大眾對生態議題的重視。更多資訊可參考: https://delta50.deltaww.com/initiative/sea.html
